
1. What is dbms

A Database Management System (DBMS) is software that enables the creation, management, and manipulation of databases. 
It allows users to store, retrieve, update, and manage data efficiently. DBMS ensures data integrity, security, and 
consistency while supporting multiple users and applications. Examples include MySQL, Oracle, and Microsoft SQL Server.


