2.Explain types of dbms , also give example of each

1.Hierarchical DBMS
Description: Data is organized in a tree-like structure with parent-child relationships. Each child record has only one parent, forming a hierarchy.
Example: IBM Information Management System (IMS)

2. Network DBMS
Description: Data is organized in a graph structure where records can have multiple parent and child relationships, allowing more complex relationships.
Example: Integrated Data Store (IDS), IDMS (Integrated Database Management System)

3. Relational DBMS (RDBMS)
Description: Data is stored in tables (relations) with rows and columns. It uses Structured Query Language (SQL) to manage and manipulate data.
Example: MySQL, Oracle DB, Microsoft SQL Server, PostgreSQL

4. Object-Oriented DBMS (OODBMS)
Description: Data is stored as objects, similar to how data is handled in object-oriented programming. It supports complex data types like images, videos, and more.
Example: ObjectDB, db4o, GemStone/S


